programme.title: Mamma Mia!
programme.desc: Hoping to meet her real father and have him walk her down the aisle, a bride secretly invites three men from her mothers (Meryl Streep) past to come to the wedding.

programme.title: Your Highness

programme.title: Gemini Man
programme.desc: Henry Brogan is an elite assassin who becomes the target of a mysterious operative who can seemingly predict his every move. To his horror, he soon learns that the man whos trying to kill him is a younger, faster, cloned version of himself.

programme.title: Terminator Genisys
programme.desc: Kyle Reese (Jai Courtney) goes back to 1984 to save Sarah Connor (Emilia Clarke) and emerges in an alternate timeline in which Sarah has been raised as a warrior by a Terminator guardian (Arnold Schwarzenegger).

programme.title: Coyote Creek Christmas
programme.desc: An event planner discovers Christmas magic with a charming father-son duo while throwing a themed Christmas party at her familys inn.

programme.title: Hollywood on Set
programme.desc: Features behind-the-scenes footage from movie sets and discussions with the cast and crew about the details of each film.

programme.title: The Christmas House 2: Deck Those Halls
programme.desc: Excited for a calm Christmas, Mike Mitchell unexpectedly gets roped into a Christmas house-decorating reality TV show against his brother.

programme.title: Dora and the Lost City of Gold
programme.desc: Accompanied by a ragtag group of teens and Boots the monkey, Dora embarks on a quest to save her parents while trying to solve the seemingly impossible mystery behind a lost Incan civilization.

programme.title: Tomb Raider
programme.desc: Hoping to solve the mystery of her fathers disappearance, young Lara Croft embarks on a perilous journey to his last-known destination -- a fabled tomb on a mythical island that might be somewhere off the coast of Japan.

programme.title: Shes the Man

programme.title: The Spy Next Door

programme.title: Around the World in 80 Days

programme.title: Hachiko: A Dogs Story
programme.desc: A college professor (Richard Gere) forms a lasting bond with a dog that he finds on a train platform.

programme.title: The Magnificent Seven
programme.desc: Desperate townspeople hire seven mercenaries (Denzel Washington, Chris Pratt, Ethan Hawke) to battle a greedy industrialist (Peter Sarsgaard) and his ruthless henchmen in the Old West.

programme.title: The Northman
programme.desc: Prince Amleth is on the verge of becoming a man when his father is brutally murdered by his uncle, who kidnaps the boys mother. Two decades later, Amleth is now a Viking whos on a mission to save his mother, kill his uncle and avenge his father.

programme.title: Live Die Repeat: Edge of Tomorrow
programme.desc: A soldier fighting aliens gets to relive the same day over and over again, the day restarting every time he dies.

programme.title: The Expendables 2

programme.title: Next Stop, Christmas

programme.title: Coyote Creek Christmas
programme.desc: An event planner discovers Christmas magic with a charming father-son duo while throwing a themed Christmas party at her familys inn.

programme.title: Happy Family
programme.desc: Draculas spell turns a woman and her loved ones into a vampire, a mummy, a werewolf and Frankensteins monster.

programme.title: The Boxtrolls

programme.title: ParaNorman
programme.desc: A ghoul-whispering youngster (Kodi Smit-McPhee) battles zombies, ghosts, witches and ignorant adults to save his town from an ancient curse.

programme.title: Dr. Seuss The Grinch

programme.title: The Addams Family

programme.title: Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald

programme.title: Fantastic Beasts: The Secrets of Dumbledore
